00:39:51.630 --> 00:39:54.420
that colleagues over at the
Digital Currency Initiative

00:39:54.420 --> 00:39:59.010
are spending a lot of time
on this question right here.

00:39:59.010 --> 00:40:01.620
And then, of course,
this is a business model.

00:40:01.620 --> 00:40:03.502
Just purely as a
venture capitalist,

00:40:03.502 --> 00:40:05.460
you have to think about,
how do I get adoption?

00:40:05.460 --> 00:40:07.770
How do-- what's my
customer user interface?

00:40:07.770 --> 00:40:10.920
I'm sure, Iman, you're thinking
a lot about this, right?

00:40:10.920 --> 00:40:13.860
You could have the best
idea on a data structure.

00:40:13.860 --> 00:40:17.460
You could have a really
nifty idea on a native token.

00:40:17.460 --> 00:40:19.590
But you still have
to deal with whatever

00:40:19.590 --> 00:40:24.270
venture capitalist has to do is,
how do I get users to use this?

00:40:24.270 --> 00:40:24.900
Adoption.

00:40:24.900 --> 00:40:27.120
What's my UI?

00:40:27.120 --> 00:40:32.310
And it's sort of a much
more generic set of issues.

00:40:32.310 --> 00:40:32.810
Iman.

00:40:32.810 --> 00:40:34.980
AUDIENCE: That was
my answer to Jihee.

00:40:34.980 --> 00:40:36.900
