I'm playing the Aleem
today, since he's not here.

01:03:54.456 --> 01:03:55.517
But there's no--

01:03:55.517 --> 01:03:56.600
GARY GENSLER: No, but we--

01:03:56.600 --> 01:03:59.670
AUDIENCE: That's been a long
solved problem of how consensus

01:03:59.670 --> 01:04:01.360
algorithms that--
or you can replicate

01:04:01.360 --> 01:04:06.380
state on the same state
on both the machines

01:04:06.380 --> 01:04:09.490
and tolerate some [INAUDIBLE]
number of failures.

01:04:09.490 --> 01:04:14.470
So I personally don't really
see the use of blockchain

01:04:14.470 --> 01:04:18.990
in permissioned systems, but
I do see a lot of potential

01:04:18.990 --> 01:04:21.780
for permissionless systems,
just because those algorithms

01:04:21.780 --> 01:04:24.540
already exist out there
to do [INAUDIBLE]..

01:04:24.540 --> 01:04:26.550
GARY GENSLER: So what
Sabrina's raising--

01:04:26.550 --> 01:04:28.410
you can take the Sabrina seat.

01:04:28.410 --> 01:04:34.060
You're-- Sabrina's a master's
student at computer science

01:04:34.060 --> 01:04:38.160
at MIT, so she probably knows
what she's talking about--

01:04:38.160 --> 01:04:41.910
is really saying, well,
you can do a lot of that.

01:04:41.910 --> 01:04:44.640
You can have
distributed databases

01:04:44.640 --> 01:04:47.250
without blockchain technology.

01:04:47.250 --> 01:04:49.380
You can have-- and
there's ways that

01:04:49.380 --> 01:04:52.380
this Byzantine-fought
tolerance has been addressed

01:04:52.380 --> 01:04:55.860
in distributed
databases that you don't

01:04:55.860 --> 01:04:57.510
need blockchain technology.

01:04:57.510 --> 01:05:02.055
The concept of a block,
commitment hash, block,

01:05:02.055 --> 01:05:06.100
a commitment hash,
block technology.

01:05:06.100 --> 01:05:07.240
And I accept that.

01:05:07.240 --> 01:05:10.890
But I'm not going
to accept it to say

01:05:10.890 --> 01:05:13.830
that there's no space for
permissioned blockchain

01:05:13.830 --> 01:05:15.510
technology.

01:05:15.510 --> 01:05:17.880
What there is space
for is the 80 of you

01:05:17.880 --> 01:05:21.760
in this room to have different
opinions on all of this.

